JOHANNESBURG - Former Hawks boss Berning Ntlemeza is fighting back.He wants a restraining order against Police Minister Fikile Mbalula.READ: 'There's a new sheriff in town' - MbalulaNtlemeza's asking the North Gauteng High Court to stop Mbalula from preventing his return to work.He argues that no court has the power to remove him from office.Ntlemeza still insists that only a parliamentary process can facilitate his axing.The axed Hawks boss says he's served the country loyally for 35-years as a policeman, and doesn't deserve to be made an object of contempt and ridicule. Tweets about @MbalulaFikile OR #Ntlemeza AND (FROM:@karynmaughan since:2017-04-25 until:2017-04-26) eNCA